    grpstr.l $e |- L
          = { <. ( Base ` ndx ) , B >. , <. ( +g ` ndx ) , P >. } $.
    $( Generalize a specific 2-element group ` L ` to show that any set ` K `
       with the same (relevant) properties is also a group. $)
    grpstr $p |- ( K e. Grp <-> L e. Grp ) $=
